{
  "texts": [
    "The segmentation relies on a fine-tuned VGG-16 to accurately classify the fossil prior to segmentation.",
    "The system relies on failure detection to handle errors at different stages (identification, classification, and others).",
    "The potential impact of cumulative errors or how errors in one stage might affect subsequent stages has not been explored.",
    "In a similar study, Ge et al. (2021) propose a homology-based detector of local structural difference between two fossil edge maps with a tolerable deformation.",
    "The proposed detector enhances the fossils' structural differences, which specialized loss functions use to assess segmentation."
  ]
}